t? You can keep your good intentions to devour every last detail, but meanwhile come join us for an illuminating talk on why we care so deeply about security as a design philosophy central to all our iOS products."}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-706-Whats-New-in-Security":{"title":"What’s New in Security","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Designing security into your app requires that you follow secure coding practices and use the security features that are built into the operating system. Learn about new developments in Security on iOS, macOS, watchOS and tvOS that impact your apps. Hear about best practices for developing and distributing secure apps and protecting people’s data."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-706-Whats-New-in-Security","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-706-whats-new-in-security","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-401-Whats-New-in-Xcode-App-Signing":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-401-Whats-New-in-Xcode-App-Signing","kind":"article","title":"What’s New in Xcode App Signing","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-401-whats-new-in-xcode-app-signing","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Xcode provides powerful options for managing projects for small and large development teams. Learn how new features in Xcode simplify the process of certificate management, app signing and configuration of your project’s build settings.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16":{"abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 8, Swift 3.0, iOS 10, macOS 10.12 (Sierra), tvOS 10, watchOS 3.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16","title":"WWDC16","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","alt":null},"WWDC16.jpeg":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes"},"WWDC16-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-709-Engineering-Privacy-for-Your-Users":{"title":"Engineering Privacy for Your Users","abstract":[{"text":"Learn about new developments in Privacy on iOS, macOS, watchOS, and tvOS that impact you and your apps. Explore techniques to respect your users’ privacy while building great features into your apps.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-709-Engineering-Privacy-for-Your-Users","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-709-engineering-privacy-for-your-users","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-701-Introducing-Apple-File-System":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-701-introducing-apple-file-system","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","title":"Introducing Apple File System","abstract":[{"text":"The Apple File System (APFS) is the next-generation file system designed to scale from an Apple Watch to a Mac Pro. APFS is optimized for Flash\/SSD storage, and engineered with encryption as a primary feature. Learn about APFS benefits versus HFS+ and how to make sure your file system code is compatible.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-701-Introducing-Apple-File-System"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Learn More…","type":"text"}]},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2016/705/":{"checksum":null,"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/705\/","url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/705\/","type":"download"}}}